Follow these steps to set the rate limit
•	Go to Jira admin setting
•	Click on system
•	Click on rate limit
•	Now click on enable set below options
•	Limit requests
	Request allowed per node : 2000 per 1 hours per user
	Max request : 2000
•	Now click on save
•	Now add exemption whom you do want to block
•	Click on add exemption
•	Select the user account or group
•	Select allow unlimited requests
•	Now click on add.
•	If you want to block you have to just select Block all requests.
